Popular media mogul, Dele Momodu, has debunked the reported death of former speaker of the House of Representative, Ghali Umar Na’ Abba. Reports had emerged on Friday morning that Na’Abba died in a hospital in London. However, Momodu took to his Twitter page confirming that the former speaker is alive and well. He disclosed that he spoke to the former Speaker personally on Friday. Momodu wrote: “Former speaker, Ghali Umar Na’ Abba is not dead as being currently speculated. “I have just spoken to him and making arrangements for him to join me soon now INSTAGRAM LIVE.” Na’ Abba served under the administration of former President, Olusegun Obasanjo, as Speaker of the House of Representatives.